        <h3>Etiquette</h3>
        <h1>Tipping </h1>
      <img src="/Usatip.jpg" alt="Football enthusiasm" class="smaller-image">
      <p>Tipping is a customary practice in the United States and an integral part of the service industry. It reflects appreciation for the quality of service received and is considered a way to recognize the hard work of servers, bartenders, taxi drivers, hotel staff, and other service providers. Tipping percentages typically range from 15% to 20% of the total bill in restaurants, depending on the level of service and the establishment's guidelines. While tipping is voluntary, it's essential to understand that many service workers rely heavily on gratuities as a significant portion of their income.</p>
    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p>As such, leaving a fair and generous tip is not only a social norm but also a way to support individuals in the service industry. It's worth noting that tipping is not limited to dining; it extends to various service encounters, from rideshares to hair salons, and even to tour guides or other individuals who enhance your experience during your visit to the USA.</p>
    </div>
    <h1>Self-Service</h1>
        <img src="/Usaselfservice.jpg" alt="Photography of People" class="smaller-image">
      <p> The concept of self-service in American restaurants reflects a cultural emphasis on convenience and customer empowerment. It's a practice deeply ingrained in the dining experience, and it's not only accepted but often expected by both diners and restaurant staff. This approach allows patrons to have greater control over their dining experience, from adding condiments and adjusting flavors to refilling beverages at their leisure. It also aligns with the fast-paced lifestyle commonly found in the United States, where efficiency and choice are highly valued.  </p>
    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p>The self-service model not only enhances convenience but also contributes to a more relaxed and enjoyable dining experience, as diners can customize their meals according to their preferences. It's a unique aspect of American dining culture that many visitors find welcoming and liberating, providing a sense of autonomy while enjoying a meal.</p>
